<TITLE> River bandits swoop on police </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, July 9 (bdnews24.com)River bandits looking for victims on the Turag river in Savar swooped on a police patrol, looted a gun and managed to escape on Thursday. Savar police chief Nasir Ullah told bdnews24.com, "We have reinforced our river patrols to curb incidents of robbery and narcotics trafficking." "A seven-member team was patrolling on the Turag this morning when a gang of robbers attacked them and an exchange of fire took place," he said. "At one point, the dacoits looted a gun from the police boat and escaped. Another police shotgun fell into the river." "Police are trying to retrieve the arms," he said. No casualties were reported. bdne
